main event: One observer reported seeing 6 to 10 bright sparks at minimum altitude with fluorescence on January 30, 1958.
interesting points: The observation was made at a minimum altitude displaying a series of sparks,The report has been classified as insufficient data for a clear conclusion,There is a historical reference to a similar sighting in 1955 in Uruguay,The authenticity of the previous photograph from 1955 has been disputed,The conclusion speculated that the observed object could be a balloon or possibly astronomical.
witness description: the observer reportedly saw the sparks at minimum altitude
